WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.340 --> 00:00:06.715
[SCREECHING]

2
00:00:07.050 --> 00:00:08.736
What are the chances

3
00:00:08.760 --> 00:00:10.905
my van hits a police car this morning?

4
00:00:10.929 --> 00:00:12.281
You gonna help me.

5
00:00:12.305 --> 00:00:14.450
Odell Morgan. What can you tell me?

6
00:00:14.474 --> 00:00:16.035
He was convicted of
killing his wife. Simone.

7
00:00:16.059 --> 00:00:17.370
Simone's body was never found.

8
00:00:17.394 --> 00:00:20.081
I did not kill my wife.

9
00:00:20.105 --> 00:00:22.291
Morgan's brother-in-law testified

10
00:00:22.315 --> 00:00:24.293
to seeing Morgan transporting
a heavy rug into his vehicle.

11
00:00:24.317 --> 00:00:25.962
Why did you lie?

12
00:00:25.986 --> 00:00:27.255
I had to.

13
00:00:27.279 --> 00:00:29.257
- They made me.
- Who are you scared of?

14
00:00:29.281 --> 00:00:30.591
Someone took him out.

15
00:00:30.615 --> 00:00:31.884
[GLASS SHATTERING]

16
00:00:31.908 --> 00:00:33.892
Someone framed Morgan.

17
00:00:34.286 --> 00:00:35.513
[SIREN WAILING]

18
00:00:35.537 --> 00:00:37.265
Wanna know who killed my wife.

19
00:00:37.289 --> 00:00:39.308
[BEEPING]

20
00:00:39.332 --> 00:00:40.977
Your dad didn't kill her.

21
00:00:41.001 --> 00:00:42.478
Who did?

22
00:00:42.502 --> 00:00:44.856
I don't know yet. but I'm gonna help.

23
00:00:44.880 --> 00:00:48.234
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

24
00:00:48.258 --> 00:00:50.737
[VOICE ECHOING] What are the chances

25
00:00:50.761 --> 00:00:54.139
that I crashed into you?

26
00:00:55.724 --> 00:00:56.808
[PEN CLICKS]

27
00:01:02.439 --> 00:01:05.209
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

28
00:01:05.233 --> 00:01:06.627
Oh. you're still here.

29
00:01:06.651 --> 00:01:08.629
I thought everyone cleared out.

30
00:01:08.653 --> 00:01:10.256
I'm looking for a new office phone.

31
00:01:10.280 --> 00:01:13.134
- Mine has gone paws up.
- In there.

32
00:01:13.158 --> 00:01:14.910
Okay.

33
00:01:25.962 --> 00:01:27.607
Simone Morgan's case.

34
00:01:27.631 --> 00:01:29.442
Anything pop?

35
00:01:29.466 --> 00:01:30.777
No.

36
00:01:30.801 --> 00:01:33.404
The more I spend on it.
the more I realize

37
00:01:33.428 --> 00:01:36.157
I keep running into the same questions.

38
00:01:36.181 --> 00:01:38.534
Cold cases always feel like that.

39
00:01:38.558 --> 00:01:40.995
Working them is an act of faith.

40
00:01:41.585 --> 00:01:43.790
Yeah. you gotta blindly
believe that someday. somehow.

41
00:01:43.814 --> 00:01:45.714
something will appear.

42
00:01:46.551 --> 00:01:47.886
A lead that was missed.

43
00:01:51.261 --> 00:01:52.930
You want help?

44
00:01:53.990 --> 00:01:56.173
Voight said I can't have
anyone helping me

45
00:01:56.197 --> 00:01:58.304
until something new pops.

46
00:01:58.328 --> 00:02:00.229
So we'll work it off hours.

47
00:02:01.123 --> 00:02:02.975
That's okay. You don't have to do that.

48
00:02:02.999 --> 00:02:04.710
You could just say thank you and let me.

49
00:02:07.671 --> 00:02:09.357
[SCOFFS] Thank you.

50
00:02:09.381 --> 00:02:10.507
Mm-hmm.

51
00:02:14.720 --> 00:02:16.030
Timeline?

52
00:02:16.054 --> 00:02:17.615
I'm working the last 36 hours

53
00:02:17.639 --> 00:02:19.158
before Simone died.

54
00:02:19.182 --> 00:02:22.709
She used to work the night
shift at a local diner.

55
00:02:23.877 --> 00:02:25.665
She worked there
the night before she died?

56
00:02:25.689 --> 00:02:26.838
Yeah.

57
00:02:27.232 --> 00:02:28.251
Typical night.

58
00:02:28.275 --> 00:02:29.794
Clocked out at 11:02 p.m.

59
00:02:29.818 --> 00:02:31.212
Walked home.

60
00:02:31.236 --> 00:02:33.423
[TENSE MUSIC]

61
00:02:33.447 --> 00:02:35.216
She always took the same path home.

62
00:02:35.240 --> 00:02:37.218
It's about an 18-minute walk.

63
00:02:37.242 --> 00:02:44.207
♪ ♪

64
00:02:52.799 --> 00:02:54.610
And she made it home. no problem.

65
00:02:54.634 --> 00:02:57.280
Yes. but she didn't go to sleep.

66
00:02:57.304 --> 00:03:00.158
Instead. she stayed up
and placed three 911 calls.

67
00:03:00.182 --> 00:03:01.200
all hang-ups.

68
00:03:01.224 --> 00:03:02.791
Any theories why?

69
00:03:03.727 --> 00:03:06.289
Original detectives thought
the 911 calls were related

70
00:03:06.313 --> 00:03:08.458
to her husband.
that they had been fighting.

71
00:03:08.482 --> 00:03:11.091
she was scared.
but we know that's not true.

72
00:03:11.116 --> 00:03:18.307
♪ ♪

73
00:03:18.825 --> 00:03:20.219
Then she wakes up the next day.

74
00:03:20.243 --> 00:03:21.454
stays home with her kid.

75
00:03:21.478 --> 00:03:23.806
takes her kid to a sleepover
at the friend's.

76
00:03:23.830 --> 00:03:25.850
Then doesn't go to work.

77
00:03:25.874 --> 00:03:28.519
Her and Odell go
to a bar instead. fight.

78
00:03:28.543 --> 00:03:31.064
He can tell something's wrong.
She seems off.

79
00:03:31.088 --> 00:03:32.899
They go home. He passes out.

80
00:03:32.923 --> 00:03:34.525
And wakes up to blood.

81
00:03:34.549 --> 00:03:37.195
Her body's gone.
but the amount of blood loss

82
00:03:37.219 --> 00:03:39.030
indicates death.

83
00:03:39.054 --> 00:03:40.907
And someone frames
Odell Morgan for her death.

84
00:03:40.931 --> 00:03:42.992
then years later. kills Carter
Thomas to cover their tracks.

85
00:03:43.016 --> 00:03:45.643
Something happened to her
in those 36 hours.

86
00:03:45.667 --> 00:03:47.205
She was fine at work. She goes home.

87
00:03:47.229 --> 00:03:48.456
She calls 911.

88
00:03:48.480 --> 00:03:49.832
Acts strange. stays home all day.

89
00:03:49.856 --> 00:03:51.667
calls out of work.
fights with her husband.

90
00:03:51.691 --> 00:03:53.151
Is killed.

91
00:03:56.029 --> 00:03:58.615
Feels like she was scared of something.

92
00:04:00.551 --> 00:04:03.554
I really don't remember
my mom being scared.

93
00:04:06.289 --> 00:04:08.857
Why are we walking this way again?

94
00:04:09.918 --> 00:04:11.860
Repetition.

95
00:04:12.129 --> 00:04:14.279
Might help jog the memory.

96
00:04:15.048 --> 00:04:18.617
I told you. I don't really
remember anything.

97
00:04:19.219 --> 00:04:21.119
I wasn't paying attention.

98
00:04:21.430 --> 00:04:22.996
You were 15.

99
00:04:23.945 --> 00:04:25.196
Of course you weren't.

100
00:04:26.977 --> 00:04:29.414
Do you remember her
being off the next day

101
00:04:29.438 --> 00:04:31.588
or her mentioning anything?

102
00:04:32.315 --> 00:04:35.300
No. I don't.

103
00:04:36.593 --> 00:04:38.756
I don't know. I'm sorry.

104
00:04:38.780 --> 00:04:40.889
There's no reason to be sorry.

105
00:04:42.033 --> 00:04:43.344
What could have happened to her?

106
00:04:43.368 --> 00:04:47.873
I mean. something that
she was murdered over?

107
00:04:53.318 --> 00:04:54.653
What?

108
00:04:55.464 --> 00:04:56.905
What is it?

109
00:04:57.674 --> 00:04:59.783
I didn't notice that before.

110
00:05:01.136 --> 00:05:02.613
A truck driver named Noah Lewis

111
00:05:02.637 --> 00:05:05.116
was shot in the chest
on that block six years ago.

112
00:05:05.140 --> 00:05:07.076
A murder.

113
00:05:07.100 --> 00:05:08.494
What date?

114
00:05:08.518 --> 00:05:09.918
Mm...

115
00:05:10.812 --> 00:05:12.623
August 22nd.

116
00:05:12.647 --> 00:05:13.750
The night before Simone was killed.

117
00:05:13.774 --> 00:05:15.043
What time?

118
00:05:15.067 --> 00:05:16.878
[TENSE MUSIC]

119
00:05:16.902 --> 00:05:18.546
Uh. gunshots were reported to 911

120
00:05:18.570 --> 00:05:21.549
from a nearby neighbor at 11:07 p.m.

121
00:05:21.573 --> 00:05:23.092
Right when Simone was walking home.

122
00:05:23.116 --> 00:05:24.343
She passed that location.

123
00:05:24.367 --> 00:05:25.702
Every single night.

124
00:05:28.705 --> 00:05:30.540
What if that's why she was killed?

125
00:05:33.210 --> 00:05:35.110
She witnessed a murder.

126
00:05:36.588 --> 00:05:44.588
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

127
00:05:44.613 --> 00:05:46.556
The night before
Simone Morgan was killed.

128
00:05:46.581 --> 00:05:48.413
a young truck driver
named Noah Lewis was

129
00:05:48.437 --> 00:05:50.578
shot and killed in a suspected
drug rip gone wrong.

130
00:05:50.602 --> 00:05:52.163
Police thought it was a rip crew.

131
00:05:52.187 --> 00:05:53.289
but they never confirmed it.

132
00:05:53.313 --> 00:05:54.874
because Noah's killer was never caught.

133
00:05:54.898 --> 00:05:56.793
How is this related to Simone's murder?

134
00:05:56.817 --> 00:05:58.920
Noah's time of death is
consistent with the exact time

135
00:05:58.944 --> 00:06:00.922
Simone would have been walking home.

136
00:06:00.946 --> 00:06:03.341
And her usual route puts her
in the exact spot

137
00:06:03.365 --> 00:06:04.967
where Noah was murdered.

138
00:06:04.991 --> 00:06:07.470
We believe that
Simone witnessed the homicide.

139
00:06:07.494 --> 00:06:09.472
- Hmm.
- Okay.

140
00:06:09.496 --> 00:06:13.476
So your theory is.
Simone saw Noah get murdered.

141
00:06:13.500 --> 00:06:14.894
Offender clocked her. tracked her down.

142
00:06:14.918 --> 00:06:15.937
and then killed her too?

143
00:06:15.961 --> 00:06:17.563
- And Carter.
- Yes.

144
00:06:17.587 --> 00:06:19.273
Offender was covering his tracks.

145
00:06:19.297 --> 00:06:21.150
I mean. it's wide. but it could fit.

146
00:06:21.174 --> 00:06:22.402
It fits.

147
00:06:22.426 --> 00:06:23.611
Why Simone was scared.

148
00:06:23.635 --> 00:06:24.946
Why she acted off the next day.

149
00:06:24.970 --> 00:06:27.532
Why she called 911. called in sick.

150
00:06:27.556 --> 00:06:30.332
She didn't know what to do.
She was panicking.

151
00:06:30.976 --> 00:06:33.204
If we're right. we ID who killed Noah.

152
00:06:33.228 --> 00:06:35.397
then we ID who killed Simone.

153
00:06:38.900 --> 00:06:40.545
It's good.

154
00:06:40.569 --> 00:06:41.843
It's enough now.

155
00:06:44.072 --> 00:06:45.800
Come on. let's all work it.

156
00:06:45.824 --> 00:06:48.386
Noah was found shot
beside his box truck.

157
00:06:48.410 --> 00:06:51.347
The truck was modified
to conceal bulk narcotics.

158
00:06:51.371 --> 00:06:53.766
and the traps were forced open
and empty of drugs

159
00:06:53.790 --> 00:06:55.435
by the time police arrived on scene.

160
00:06:55.459 --> 00:06:57.270
So was Noah affiliated?

161
00:06:57.294 --> 00:06:59.856
Yeah. documented G-Park.

162
00:06:59.880 --> 00:07:01.733
DEA had his truck indexed.

163
00:07:01.757 --> 00:07:04.110
Electronic homicide file
was pretty thin.

164
00:07:04.134 --> 00:07:05.737
None of the handwritten
GPRs were in there.

165
00:07:05.761 --> 00:07:08.448
Yeah. but originals should
still be with the Area Cold Case.

166
00:07:08.472 --> 00:07:09.991
Yep. Area 1.

167
00:07:10.015 --> 00:07:11.498
I'll be back.

168
00:07:12.392 --> 00:07:14.519
You think that's why she was killed?

169
00:07:15.979 --> 00:07:17.832
She witnessed a murder?

170
00:07:17.856 --> 00:07:20.340
Do you remember hearing
the name Noah Lewis?

171
00:07:21.193 --> 00:07:23.760
No. I don't think so.

172
00:07:28.283 --> 00:07:29.808
This is him.

173
00:07:31.027 --> 00:07:32.862
Do you recognize him?

174
00:07:34.498 --> 00:07:35.999
No.

175
00:07:38.168 --> 00:07:40.438
My mom saw this kid die?

176
00:07:40.462 --> 00:07:43.649
That's so awful.
I mean. she must have been terrified.

177
00:07:43.673 --> 00:07:47.528
It's still just a theory.
but it feels good to me.

178
00:07:47.552 --> 00:07:48.720
Good?

179
00:07:50.097 --> 00:07:51.329
Right.

180
00:07:52.371 --> 00:07:53.830
It feels right.

181
00:07:55.102 --> 00:07:57.330
[KNOCKING]

182
00:07:57.354 --> 00:07:58.956
Hey. sorry.

183
00:07:58.980 --> 00:08:00.750
Uh. lead detective on Noah's case

184
00:08:00.774 --> 00:08:02.543
died from cancer last year.

185
00:08:02.567 --> 00:08:04.045
but all the files are in Area 1.

186
00:08:04.069 --> 00:08:05.505
so I told them we'd be coming by.

187
00:08:05.529 --> 00:08:07.155
All right. Thank you.

188
00:08:12.869 --> 00:08:17.433
Look. um. I gotta go.

189
00:08:17.457 --> 00:08:18.851
I'll call you as soon as I know more.

190
00:08:18.875 --> 00:08:20.692
You can call me anytime.

191
00:08:22.017 --> 00:08:23.185
Okay.

192
00:08:31.179 --> 00:08:33.246
All these unsolved murders.

193
00:08:34.099 --> 00:08:35.868
Families without closure.

194
00:08:35.892 --> 00:08:37.203
Yeah.

195
00:08:37.227 --> 00:08:38.788
Most of these people spend
their whole lives

196
00:08:38.812 --> 00:08:40.373
waiting for answers they'll never get.

197
00:08:40.397 --> 00:08:42.041
And this is just Area 1.

198
00:08:42.065 --> 00:08:43.358
This way.

199
00:08:45.944 --> 00:08:49.448
Should be here.

200
00:08:52.826 --> 00:08:54.286
Here. take this one.

201
00:09:02.586 --> 00:09:04.087
Okay.

202
00:09:14.556 --> 00:09:16.581
The handwritten notes here.

203
00:09:19.416 --> 00:09:20.876
Person of interest log.

204
00:09:26.068 --> 00:09:27.569
Lead detective was thorough.

205
00:09:29.552 --> 00:09:30.882
Noted every person he spoke to.

206
00:09:30.906 --> 00:09:32.491
even the ones that went nowhere.

207
00:09:40.499 --> 00:09:42.000
Hey. can you read this?

208
00:09:46.171 --> 00:09:50.509
Looks like "talk to Marcus again."

209
00:09:51.968 --> 00:09:53.576
Who's Marcus?

210
00:09:54.179 --> 00:09:55.490
I don't know. there's...

211
00:09:55.514 --> 00:09:57.575
there's a bunch of Marcuses listed here.

212
00:09:57.599 --> 00:09:59.082
Let me see.

213
00:09:59.851 --> 00:10:03.915
The lead detective might
be dead. but chances are.

214
00:10:03.939 --> 00:10:06.691
he hooked in the reporting
officer assigned to the beat.

215
00:10:11.876 --> 00:10:13.336
Brian Foster.

216
00:10:14.866 --> 00:10:17.220
- Detective Foster.
- Yeah.

217
00:10:17.244 --> 00:10:20.038
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

218
00:10:22.999 --> 00:10:24.310
Torres. Intelligence.

219
00:10:24.334 --> 00:10:25.978
Oh. hey. Voight's guys.

220
00:10:26.002 --> 00:10:27.855
- Imani.
- Uh. listen.

221
00:10:27.879 --> 00:10:30.191
This poor bastard got
choked out in broad daylight.

222
00:10:30.215 --> 00:10:32.193
I got six witnesses; they're all high.

223
00:10:32.217 --> 00:10:33.653
So I can give you five minutes.

224
00:10:33.677 --> 00:10:34.654
Good?

225
00:10:34.678 --> 00:10:35.738
Mind?

226
00:10:35.762 --> 00:10:37.323
People get all weird these days.

227
00:10:37.347 --> 00:10:39.283
So we're looking into
the Noah Lewis case.

228
00:10:39.307 --> 00:10:40.952
It's a truck driver that got shot and...

229
00:10:40.976 --> 00:10:44.747
Yeah. was whacked outside
his truck in Bronzeville?

230
00:10:44.771 --> 00:10:46.249
Yeah. I remember it.

231
00:10:46.273 --> 00:10:47.291
I was assigned to that beat back then.

232
00:10:47.315 --> 00:10:48.960
It was a dope rip gone wrong.

233
00:10:48.984 --> 00:10:49.961
Kid was young.

234
00:10:49.985 --> 00:10:51.676
Was a damn shame.

235
00:10:52.195 --> 00:10:53.822
Yeah. are these your notes?

236
00:10:54.990 --> 00:10:56.718
Yeah. that's my handwriting.

237
00:10:56.742 --> 00:10:59.387
I was first officer on scene
that night. did the paper.

238
00:10:59.411 --> 00:11:01.848
Do you recall who Marcus was?

239
00:11:01.872 --> 00:11:04.308
Uh. "talk to Marcus again."

240
00:11:04.332 --> 00:11:06.561
No. I don't remember any Marcus.

241
00:11:06.585 --> 00:11:08.813
What the hell are you guys
doing with that old case anyway?

242
00:11:08.837 --> 00:11:10.023
Well. we believe Noah Lewis has

243
00:11:10.047 --> 00:11:11.733
a connection with two other homicides.

244
00:11:11.757 --> 00:11:13.943
Simone Morgan and Carter Thomas.

245
00:11:13.967 --> 00:11:15.445
Yeah. never heard of them.

246
00:11:15.469 --> 00:11:17.030
but I appreciate the commitment.

247
00:11:17.054 --> 00:11:19.073
All right? Been there before myself.

248
00:11:19.097 --> 00:11:20.658
Locked in on a case that went nowhere.

249
00:11:20.682 --> 00:11:23.453
So no idea who this Marcus was

250
00:11:23.477 --> 00:11:24.996
or why you wanted to speak to him again?

251
00:11:25.020 --> 00:11:26.456
Nah. sorry.

252
00:11:26.480 --> 00:11:27.957
You know. we interviewed
dozens of G-Park Lords.

253
00:11:27.981 --> 00:11:29.208
No one said a thing.

254
00:11:29.232 --> 00:11:30.710
They closed rank. right?

255
00:11:30.734 --> 00:11:32.795
Seemed like they...
they knew who committed the rip

256
00:11:32.819 --> 00:11:34.112
and wanted street justice.

257
00:11:35.947 --> 00:11:36.966
Did they get it?

258
00:11:36.990 --> 00:11:38.468
Probably.

259
00:11:38.492 --> 00:11:39.886
I mean. chances are.
whoever killed that poor kid

260
00:11:39.910 --> 00:11:41.054
is long dead and buried

261
00:11:41.078 --> 00:11:42.388
at the bottom of a lake somewhere.

262
00:11:42.412 --> 00:11:43.514
Right.

263
00:11:43.538 --> 00:11:44.766
[YELLING IN DISTANCE]

264
00:11:44.790 --> 00:11:46.601
I gotta go. but any other questions

265
00:11:46.625 --> 00:11:48.441
come up. you just give me a holler. hmm?

266
00:11:49.044 --> 00:11:50.563
- All right. Thank you.
- Thank you for your time.

267
00:11:50.587 --> 00:11:52.607
Mm-hmm.

268
00:11:52.631 --> 00:11:55.360
[SIGHS]

269
00:11:55.384 --> 00:11:56.802
Dante. you got ears on?

270
00:11:59.721 --> 00:12:01.157
Yeah. go ahead.

271
00:12:01.181 --> 00:12:03.117
I ran all the Marcuses you gave me.
I got one possible.

272
00:12:03.141 --> 00:12:05.328
His name is Marcus Lee.

273
00:12:05.352 --> 00:12:06.829
He's listed in the gang database

274
00:12:06.853 --> 00:12:08.247
and your personal logbook.

275
00:12:08.271 --> 00:12:10.416
He was in the G-Park six years ago.

276
00:12:10.440 --> 00:12:12.960
Young. but listed as
an enforcer for their runners.

277
00:12:12.984 --> 00:12:14.045
All right. that fits.

278
00:12:14.069 --> 00:12:15.213
Uh. what's his status?

279
00:12:15.237 --> 00:12:16.964
Uh. he got no status now.

280
00:12:16.988 --> 00:12:19.217
The G-Parks cut ties 'cause
he got high off his own supply.

281
00:12:19.241 --> 00:12:20.468
He's been arrested multiple times

282
00:12:20.492 --> 00:12:22.595
for possession and solicitation.

283
00:12:22.619 --> 00:12:23.596
So he might talk now?

284
00:12:23.620 --> 00:12:24.806
Yeah.

285
00:12:24.830 --> 00:12:26.808
His LKA was knocked down two years ago.

286
00:12:26.832 --> 00:12:29.477
but he's known to work
an old lot on 16th and Cicero.

287
00:12:29.501 --> 00:12:31.025
Could be worth a shot.

288
00:12:31.837 --> 00:12:35.817
[RUMBLING]

289
00:12:35.841 --> 00:12:37.735
Approaching the back door now.

290
00:12:37.759 --> 00:12:40.321
Copy you. Ocean. We got your six.

291
00:12:40.345 --> 00:12:43.282
[TENSE MUSIC]

292
00:12:43.306 --> 00:12:50.272
♪ ♪

293
00:13:27.934 --> 00:13:28.934
Here we go.

294
00:13:32.981 --> 00:13:34.631
What's up. man?

295
00:13:35.692 --> 00:13:37.003
Who you talking to?

296
00:13:37.027 --> 00:13:38.129
I'm talking to you. man.

297
00:13:38.153 --> 00:13:39.464
I'm looking at you.

298
00:13:39.488 --> 00:13:41.424
Oh. you friendly now. huh?

299
00:13:41.448 --> 00:13:43.384
Well. I ain't. so keep it
pushing with your friendly ass.

300
00:13:43.408 --> 00:13:44.761
Wanna be friends now?

301
00:13:44.785 --> 00:13:46.637
Got some good dope.

302
00:13:46.661 --> 00:13:48.997
Show me what you got.
I'll give you a good deal.

303
00:13:53.733 --> 00:13:55.104
Who the hell are you

304
00:13:55.128 --> 00:13:56.314
and why the hell you think
you can sling here?

305
00:13:56.338 --> 00:13:57.607
Chill. bro.

306
00:13:57.631 --> 00:13:59.108
I'ma show you how chill I get.

307
00:13:59.132 --> 00:14:00.842
Let's go get him.

308
00:14:02.302 --> 00:14:04.739
[GRUNTING]

309
00:14:04.763 --> 00:14:06.390
[BLOWS LANDING]

310
00:14:08.809 --> 00:14:10.703
Don't move! Hey!

311
00:14:10.727 --> 00:14:13.164
I got one in custody.
Target took off to the south side

312
00:14:13.188 --> 00:14:14.165
of the building wearing a gray shirt.

313
00:14:14.189 --> 00:14:15.124
Chicago PD.

314
00:14:15.148 --> 00:14:16.209
Hey. stop!

315
00:14:16.233 --> 00:14:17.752
Stop.

316
00:14:17.776 --> 00:14:19.670
[GRUNTS]

317
00:14:19.694 --> 00:14:21.798
Stop. stop moving.

318
00:14:21.822 --> 00:14:23.007
Put your hands out.

319
00:14:23.031 --> 00:14:24.092
Calm your ass down.

320
00:14:24.116 --> 00:14:25.200
We got you now.

321
00:14:31.410 --> 00:14:33.412
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

322
00:14:34.084 --> 00:14:35.853
2019?

323
00:14:35.877 --> 00:14:37.563
You asking me about
something from six years ago?

324
00:14:37.587 --> 00:14:38.981
What's the statute of limitations?

325
00:14:39.005 --> 00:14:40.817
We know you were with the G-Parks then.

326
00:14:40.841 --> 00:14:42.860
We know you were
overseeing their runners.

327
00:14:42.884 --> 00:14:44.779
One of them was Noah Lewis.

328
00:14:44.803 --> 00:14:45.947
I told you. I don't know who Noah is.

329
00:14:45.971 --> 00:14:47.323
And I told you. I don't believe you.

330
00:14:47.347 --> 00:14:48.825
It was years ago.

331
00:14:48.849 --> 00:14:50.493
I don't even remember
who I was back then.

332
00:14:50.517 --> 00:14:51.744
There's not much standing between you

333
00:14:51.768 --> 00:14:52.870
and getting out of here.

334
00:14:52.894 --> 00:14:54.372
but we got 48 hours to hold you.

335
00:14:54.396 --> 00:14:56.671
That is a long time to go
before you're getting well.

336
00:14:57.399 --> 00:14:58.835
It was August 22nd.

337
00:14:58.859 --> 00:15:00.336
Someone ripped off
Noah's truck and killed him.

338
00:15:00.360 --> 00:15:01.445
Who?

339
00:15:03.572 --> 00:15:06.551
You helping right now could
help solve three murders.

340
00:15:06.575 --> 00:15:07.844
You said three?

341
00:15:07.868 --> 00:15:09.262
Whoever killed that young truck driver

342
00:15:09.286 --> 00:15:10.888
also killed two other people.

343
00:15:10.912 --> 00:15:12.247
one of them a young mother.

344
00:15:17.335 --> 00:15:18.730
Listen.

345
00:15:18.754 --> 00:15:20.231
You're down on your luck right now.

346
00:15:20.255 --> 00:15:21.983
You're feeling sick. useless.

347
00:15:22.007 --> 00:15:23.162
I get it.

348
00:15:23.186 --> 00:15:25.278
But I promise you.
right now. you're not.

349
00:15:25.302 --> 00:15:27.410
Right now. you can help.

350
00:15:28.176 --> 00:15:30.095
And I won't forget it.

351
00:15:33.351 --> 00:15:34.662
That old rip was an inside job.

352
00:15:34.686 --> 00:15:36.497
I thought that then. I think that now.

353
00:15:36.521 --> 00:15:37.999
An inside job by the G-Parks?

354
00:15:38.023 --> 00:15:39.125
Yeah. man. that's what I'm saying.

355
00:15:39.149 --> 00:15:40.585
Okay. why do you think that?

356
00:15:40.609 --> 00:15:42.503
The G-Parks was a mess back then.

357
00:15:42.527 --> 00:15:45.339
- Okay.
- Fighting. beefing.

358
00:15:45.363 --> 00:15:47.597
There was this one guy who was shut out

359
00:15:48.408 --> 00:15:50.762
because he kept slipping up. kept lying.

360
00:15:50.786 --> 00:15:52.435
Okay. Who?

361
00:15:53.751 --> 00:15:55.503
We need a name.

362
00:15:58.627 --> 00:15:59.979
Darrell Jenkins.

363
00:16:00.003 --> 00:16:01.314
Long rap. mostly armed robbery

364
00:16:01.338 --> 00:16:02.732
and aggravated assault.

365
00:16:02.756 --> 00:16:04.317
He was with the G-Parks
since he was a teenager.

366
00:16:04.341 --> 00:16:06.110
Now. Marcus's story checks out.

367
00:16:06.134 --> 00:16:08.613
Darrell was beefing
with the higher-ups in 2019.

368
00:16:08.637 --> 00:16:10.198
and we got Gang Intel's evidence

369
00:16:10.222 --> 00:16:11.574
and text records of it.

370
00:16:11.598 --> 00:16:14.494
And after Noah's murder.
Darrell disappeared.

371
00:16:14.518 --> 00:16:15.578
Guy either died or went to ground.

372
00:16:15.602 --> 00:16:16.913
There's zero trace of him.

373
00:16:16.937 --> 00:16:19.082
If Darrell killed Noah.
the G-Parks knew.

374
00:16:19.106 --> 00:16:21.376
Hell. he'll be a dead man
if he didn't disappear.

375
00:16:21.400 --> 00:16:22.877
According to the Cook County docket.

376
00:16:22.901 --> 00:16:25.213
he's got an active bench
warrant for an old drug case.

377
00:16:25.237 --> 00:16:27.173
- Any known associates?
- No.

378
00:16:27.197 --> 00:16:28.883
- No family either.
- All right.

379
00:16:28.907 --> 00:16:29.967
Well. keep digging until you find

380
00:16:29.991 --> 00:16:31.135
someone who knows something.

381
00:16:31.159 --> 00:16:33.221
Wait. wait.

382
00:16:33.245 --> 00:16:34.764
He's got a cousin. Larry Moore.

383
00:16:34.788 --> 00:16:37.392
He's been dead four years.
but he's got water.

384
00:16:37.416 --> 00:16:39.060
gas. and electric bills in his name

385
00:16:39.084 --> 00:16:40.520
in a back unit apartment in Englewood.

386
00:16:40.544 --> 00:16:41.712
Go.

387
00:16:43.588 --> 00:16:46.567
[TENSE MUSIC]

388
00:16:46.591 --> 00:16:53.324
♪ ♪

389
00:16:53.348 --> 00:16:55.493
Approaching the back unit now.

390
00:16:55.517 --> 00:16:57.078
Copy you. Front's secure.

391
00:16:57.102 --> 00:17:04.109
♪ ♪

392
00:17:12.117 --> 00:17:13.886
We got movement in the garage.

393
00:17:13.910 --> 00:17:15.179
[CAR ENGINE TURNS OVER]

394
00:17:15.203 --> 00:17:16.203
Copy you.

395
00:17:20.250 --> 00:17:21.602
Chicago PD!

396
00:17:21.626 --> 00:17:23.229
Turn off the vehicle and get out.

397
00:17:23.253 --> 00:17:24.629
Turn it off!

398
00:17:27.716 --> 00:17:29.134
Hey. stop!

399
00:17:31.470 --> 00:17:32.780
Turn off the vehicle right now!

400
00:17:32.804 --> 00:17:33.972
Hands up!

401
00:17:36.224 --> 00:17:38.327
- Gun.
- Got it.

402
00:17:38.351 --> 00:17:39.876
Get out.

403
00:17:40.312 --> 00:17:41.789
Get down.

404
00:17:41.813 --> 00:17:42.749
You got anything that can hurt me?

405
00:17:42.773 --> 00:17:43.833
No.

406
00:17:43.857 --> 00:17:45.126
Get your hands behind your back.

407
00:17:45.150 --> 00:17:46.419
Hands behind your back. Don't move.

408
00:17:46.443 --> 00:17:47.420
I'm not fighting you.

409
00:17:47.444 --> 00:17:49.422
Just get me off of the street.

410
00:17:49.446 --> 00:17:50.631
He was all packed up

411
00:17:50.655 --> 00:17:51.799
like he knew you were coming. Ocean.

412
00:17:51.823 --> 00:17:53.092
I said. get me off the street!

413
00:17:53.116 --> 00:17:54.640
I heard you. Get up.

414
00:17:58.538 --> 00:17:59.891
- Get me off the street.
- What do you mean?

415
00:17:59.915 --> 00:18:01.476
- What are you talking about?
- Get me someplace safe.

416
00:18:01.500 --> 00:18:02.935
- Why?
- He's gonna kill me.

417
00:18:02.959 --> 00:18:04.604
Okay? Get me out of here.

418
00:18:04.628 --> 00:18:06.439
Wait. wait. wait. wait. who?

419
00:18:06.463 --> 00:18:09.067
I'm a dead man if y'all don't listen.

420
00:18:09.091 --> 00:18:10.985
He's gonna kill me.

421
00:18:11.009 --> 00:18:14.072
He's gonna kill me. Please. please.

422
00:18:14.096 --> 00:18:15.823
He's gonna kill me.

423
00:18:15.847 --> 00:18:22.455
♪ ♪

424
00:18:22.479 --> 00:18:24.123
All right. get out.

425
00:18:24.147 --> 00:18:25.190
Come on.

426
00:18:27.692 --> 00:18:28.944
Inside.

427
00:18:31.405 --> 00:18:32.423
All right.

428
00:18:32.447 --> 00:18:34.926
You got what you asked for. Now talk.

429
00:18:34.950 --> 00:18:36.594
- Who can come down here?
- Nobody.

430
00:18:36.618 --> 00:18:37.595
How do I know that's true?

431
00:18:37.619 --> 00:18:39.263
Because he's telling you.

432
00:18:39.287 --> 00:18:41.145
What is going on?

433
00:18:42.124 --> 00:18:43.810
You don't talk. we lead you
right back outside.

434
00:18:43.834 --> 00:18:45.269
I need a deal.

435
00:18:45.787 --> 00:18:47.122
For what?

436
00:18:48.046 --> 00:18:49.941
Ripping that G-Park truck six years ago?

437
00:18:49.965 --> 00:18:51.359
Killing Noah Lewis.
Simone Morgan. Carter Thomas?

438
00:18:51.383 --> 00:18:53.653
I didn't kill nobody.

439
00:18:53.677 --> 00:18:54.779
Now. why would we believe that?

440
00:18:54.803 --> 00:18:56.531
Because it's true.

441
00:18:56.555 --> 00:18:59.158
I ripped a couple of trucks.
yeah. but I didn't kill nobody.

442
00:18:59.182 --> 00:19:00.535
And I want a deal saying that.

443
00:19:00.559 --> 00:19:02.620
I want a deal that's gonna protect me.

444
00:19:02.777 --> 00:19:04.028
From who?

445
00:19:11.027 --> 00:19:12.422
Three people lost their lives.

446
00:19:12.446 --> 00:19:14.549
and you thought you were
about to lose yours.

447
00:19:14.573 --> 00:19:17.659
You're not safe until
we choose to protect you.

448
00:19:21.563 --> 00:19:23.020
Tell me who.

449
00:19:29.027 --> 00:19:30.528
Brian Foster.

450
00:19:32.591 --> 00:19:34.193
Detective Brian Foster?

451
00:19:34.217 --> 00:19:35.486
Yes.

452
00:19:35.510 --> 00:19:37.739
[TENSE MUSIC]

453
00:19:37.763 --> 00:19:38.948
Don't look at me like that. all right?

454
00:19:38.972 --> 00:19:40.158
It's true.

455
00:19:40.579 --> 00:19:41.951
He was working Bronzeville.

456
00:19:41.975 --> 00:19:43.411
He busted me once.

457
00:19:43.435 --> 00:19:44.954
One thing led to another.

458
00:19:44.978 --> 00:19:47.081
and we was working together. all right?

459
00:19:47.105 --> 00:19:48.124
I knew what the trucks was holding.

460
00:19:48.148 --> 00:19:49.441
I knew the routes.

461
00:19:49.465 --> 00:19:50.752
I would tell Foster the when
and the where and...

462
00:19:50.776 --> 00:19:51.794
He'd rip them with you?

463
00:19:51.818 --> 00:19:53.296
Yes.

464
00:19:53.320 --> 00:19:55.298
He'd pull them over like a traffic stop.

465
00:19:55.322 --> 00:19:58.509
I would rip the dope. but it went wrong.

466
00:19:58.533 --> 00:20:00.178
All right? Kid fought back.

467
00:20:00.202 --> 00:20:01.953
I saw Foster shoot him down.

468
00:20:04.122 --> 00:20:05.354
Foster?

469
00:20:05.874 --> 00:20:07.732
I'm telling you the truth.

470
00:20:07.757 --> 00:20:11.427
♪ ♪

471
00:20:17.803 --> 00:20:21.345
I mean. he says he was tipped
off by a call from Foster

472
00:20:21.640 --> 00:20:23.618
45 minutes before we showed up.

473
00:20:23.642 --> 00:20:25.536
He says Foster didn't want him
talking to cops.

474
00:20:25.560 --> 00:20:27.789
is convinced Foster would have
eventually killed him

475
00:20:27.813 --> 00:20:29.503
after the heat died down.

476
00:20:30.273 --> 00:20:32.126
The number who called him was a burner?

477
00:20:32.150 --> 00:20:33.836
Yes. Burner is off now.

478
00:20:33.860 --> 00:20:35.713
so we can't confirm it was really him.

479
00:20:35.737 --> 00:20:38.466
but Darrell does sound legitimate.

480
00:20:38.490 --> 00:20:40.385
He also lived under
an alias for six years.

481
00:20:40.409 --> 00:20:41.969
so clearly he's good at lying.

482
00:20:41.993 --> 00:20:43.763
He's also a really bad
cooperating defendant

483
00:20:43.787 --> 00:20:45.348
with zero solid proof.

484
00:20:45.372 --> 00:20:46.891
Who just put himself
at the scene of a crime

485
00:20:46.915 --> 00:20:48.309
of armed robbery and a murder.

486
00:20:48.333 --> 00:20:49.727
It's the word of a convicted felon

487
00:20:49.751 --> 00:20:51.104
versus a Homicide detective.

488
00:20:51.128 --> 00:20:52.188
But it fits.

489
00:20:52.212 --> 00:20:53.189
It all fits.

490
00:20:53.213 --> 00:20:54.691
Simone was scared.

491
00:20:54.715 --> 00:20:55.733
She didn't tell her husband.

492
00:20:55.757 --> 00:20:56.818
She didn't go to work.

493
00:20:56.842 --> 00:20:58.945
She hung up on the police three times.

494
00:20:58.969 --> 00:21:00.951
Who would scare her more than a cop?

495
00:21:02.514 --> 00:21:04.701
Odell Morgan was framed... well...

496
00:21:04.725 --> 00:21:06.869
and it was a long-range shot
that killed Carter Thomas.

497
00:21:06.893 --> 00:21:08.955
Which could indicate police skill set.

498
00:21:08.979 --> 00:21:10.832
And it was Detective Brian Foster.

499
00:21:10.856 --> 00:21:13.042
the only cop that knew
that we had reopened the case.

500
00:21:13.066 --> 00:21:15.169
We're gonna need a hell
of a lot more than this.

501
00:21:15.193 --> 00:21:16.550
I'm sorry.

502
00:21:17.195 --> 00:21:19.345
All right. we can move forward. but...

503
00:21:20.240 --> 00:21:23.994
unless we get something
concrete. we move real quiet.

504
00:21:26.288 --> 00:21:28.975
All right. first thing. get
Darrell's statement on record.

505
00:21:28.999 --> 00:21:30.709
Dante.

506
00:21:32.127 --> 00:21:34.439
See if Dominique recognizes Foster.

507
00:21:34.463 --> 00:21:35.672
Hmm?

508
00:21:40.385 --> 00:21:41.385
[KNOCKING]

509
00:21:48.310 --> 00:21:49.579
Hey. Maria.

510
00:21:49.603 --> 00:21:51.205
Is Dominique here?

511
00:21:51.229 --> 00:21:52.814
Uh...

512
00:21:55.525 --> 00:21:57.049
Is everything okay?

513
00:22:05.452 --> 00:22:08.056
Sarge. I found her.

514
00:22:08.080 --> 00:22:10.165
She's okay. but stand by.

515
00:22:20.133 --> 00:22:21.510
Dominique?

516
00:22:23.470 --> 00:22:25.490
What are you doing here?

517
00:22:25.514 --> 00:22:27.367
How did you find me?

518
00:22:27.778 --> 00:22:30.207
You share your location
with your roommate.

519
00:22:41.738 --> 00:22:44.616
[SHIP'S HORN BLOWING]

520
00:22:51.706 --> 00:22:53.792
My dad used to take me here.

521
00:22:56.503 --> 00:22:58.296
He loved the boats.

522
00:23:01.925 --> 00:23:03.782
I don't even know why.

523
00:23:04.678 --> 00:23:06.263
I never asked him.

524
00:23:09.808 --> 00:23:13.454
Your dad used to work
with boats in the summer

525
00:23:13.478 --> 00:23:15.377
when he was 16.

526
00:23:16.148 --> 00:23:18.108
Maybe that's why he liked them.

527
00:23:20.360 --> 00:23:22.259
[CRYING] I didn't know that.

528
00:23:23.864 --> 00:23:26.467
I didn't know that about my own father.

529
00:23:26.491 --> 00:23:28.219
You didn't get the time to know him.

530
00:23:28.243 --> 00:23:30.287
I didn't wanna know.

531
00:23:32.038 --> 00:23:34.058
I hated him!

532
00:23:34.082 --> 00:23:35.893
[SOMBER MUSIC]

533
00:23:35.917 --> 00:23:39.272
For six years. I hated him.

534
00:23:39.296 --> 00:23:41.941
♪ ♪

535
00:23:41.965 --> 00:23:44.926
[CRYING]

536
00:23:46.261 --> 00:23:49.119
Nothing makes sense anymore.

537
00:23:50.474 --> 00:23:52.748
What I thought I knew

538
00:23:53.518 --> 00:23:57.856
about my parents and my life...

539
00:23:59.941 --> 00:24:02.277
None of it makes sense now.

540
00:24:04.446 --> 00:24:06.156
It's like up is down.

541
00:24:08.950 --> 00:24:09.969
I get that.

542
00:24:09.993 --> 00:24:12.204
How can you get that?

543
00:24:13.789 --> 00:24:14.849
I know what it feels like

544
00:24:14.873 --> 00:24:16.809
when nothing makes sense anymore.

545
00:24:16.833 --> 00:24:23.799
♪ ♪

546
00:24:27.386 --> 00:24:29.388
What am I supposed to do now?

547
00:24:32.391 --> 00:24:33.725
I don't know.

548
00:24:38.897 --> 00:24:40.232
What did you do?

549
00:24:43.402 --> 00:24:45.737
I met your dad.

550
00:24:50.659 --> 00:24:52.975
He never lost his faith.

551
00:24:53.620 --> 00:24:54.931
Never.

552
00:24:54.955 --> 00:24:56.729
No one believed him.

553
00:24:57.457 --> 00:25:01.378
but he just kept on going.

554
00:25:05.549 --> 00:25:07.175
So...

555
00:25:10.053 --> 00:25:12.703
I guess we keep on going.

556
00:25:12.728 --> 00:25:19.610
♪ ♪

557
00:25:28.405 --> 00:25:30.299
I didn't realize how hungry I was.

558
00:25:30.323 --> 00:25:32.260
[CHUCKLES]

559
00:25:32.284 --> 00:25:34.095
Who taught you to cook?

560
00:25:34.119 --> 00:25:35.221
My mom.

561
00:25:35.245 --> 00:25:37.014
Mm.

562
00:25:37.038 --> 00:25:38.182
My mom liked to cook.

563
00:25:38.206 --> 00:25:39.875
- Yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

564
00:25:42.335 --> 00:25:45.231
I mean. I did come here
earlier because I wanted to...

565
00:25:45.255 --> 00:25:46.983
Oh. God. you have something. don't you?

566
00:25:47.007 --> 00:25:48.609
Yeah. [CHUCKLES]

567
00:25:48.633 --> 00:25:51.195
- And I just completely...
- No. no. It's okay.

568
00:25:51.219 --> 00:25:52.864
Is it all right if I show you something?

569
00:25:52.888 --> 00:25:54.365
Yeah. yeah.

570
00:25:54.389 --> 00:25:56.200
All right.

571
00:25:56.224 --> 00:25:58.727
Do you recognize anyone here?

572
00:26:03.648 --> 00:26:04.983
Mm...

573
00:26:14.367 --> 00:26:15.766
No.

574
00:26:16.828 --> 00:26:18.765
Sorry. I don't.

575
00:26:19.129 --> 00:26:20.481
Okay.

576
00:26:20.532 --> 00:26:21.867
It's okay.

577
00:26:31.009 --> 00:26:33.738
[WATER RUNNING]

578
00:26:33.762 --> 00:26:35.323
Hey. wait.

579
00:26:35.347 --> 00:26:36.912
He looks...

580
00:26:38.183 --> 00:26:40.620
he didn't have on the uniform. but...

581
00:26:40.644 --> 00:26:41.788
Who?

582
00:26:41.812 --> 00:26:44.791
I think this man. he was there.

583
00:26:44.815 --> 00:26:47.085
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

584
00:26:47.109 --> 00:26:49.133
The night my mom died.

585
00:26:49.820 --> 00:26:53.011
She walked me to a friend's
house for a sleepover. and...

586
00:26:54.825 --> 00:26:56.636
I think he was there.

587
00:26:56.660 --> 00:26:58.203
♪ ♪

588
00:27:03.010 --> 00:27:04.542
She remembers him.

589
00:27:04.567 --> 00:27:05.814
He was outside her friend's house

590
00:27:05.838 --> 00:27:07.355
in plain clothes. watching her mom.

591
00:27:07.379 --> 00:27:08.731
Simone didn't see.

592
00:27:08.755 --> 00:27:10.066
And Dominique at the time.
she shrugged it off

593
00:27:10.090 --> 00:27:11.526
as him being a neighbor or something.

594
00:27:11.550 --> 00:27:14.654
but that was Foster ID'ing
Simone for the first time.

595
00:27:14.678 --> 00:27:16.155
He was following her.

596
00:27:16.179 --> 00:27:18.032
We did a cell tower dump. confirmed it.

597
00:27:18.056 --> 00:27:19.826
Brian Foster's phone was
there near the friend's house.

598
00:27:19.850 --> 00:27:21.160
turned off an hour later.

599
00:27:21.184 --> 00:27:23.663
And it was his RDO. He wasn't on shift.

600
00:27:23.687 --> 00:27:25.456
There was no good reason
for him to be in that area.

601
00:27:25.480 --> 00:27:26.791
Still a hell a lot of room in that.

602
00:27:26.815 --> 00:27:28.459
I got more.

603
00:27:28.483 --> 00:27:31.295
So Dominique also told me
that Foster was watching her

604
00:27:31.319 --> 00:27:34.340
from a vehicle... a nice one.
which makes no sense.

605
00:27:34.364 --> 00:27:36.801
because Foster was
a beat cop at the time.

606
00:27:36.825 --> 00:27:38.803
But I found this.

607
00:27:38.827 --> 00:27:41.556
He bought a Porsche. paid for it in cash

608
00:27:41.580 --> 00:27:44.684
in his cousin's name.
made all service appointments.

609
00:27:44.708 --> 00:27:46.978
That's a $75.000 car.

610
00:27:47.002 --> 00:27:49.022
Foster didn't make that cash
from pushing a beat car.

611
00:27:49.046 --> 00:27:51.320
That cash was from drug rips.

612
00:27:54.259 --> 00:27:55.903
All right. do we have anything else?

613
00:27:55.927 --> 00:27:57.822
We did confirm Darrell's alibis

614
00:27:57.846 --> 00:27:59.782
for Simone and Carter's murders.

615
00:27:59.806 --> 00:28:01.784
We also confirmed that
he was arrested by Foster

616
00:28:01.808 --> 00:28:03.578
eight months prior to Noah's homicide.

617
00:28:03.602 --> 00:28:05.163
released without charges.

618
00:28:05.187 --> 00:28:07.582
Darrell's claims about
the drug rips do seem legit.

619
00:28:07.606 --> 00:28:09.333
but we don't have anything tangible

620
00:28:09.357 --> 00:28:12.545
that ties Foster to the crimes
other than Darrell's word.

621
00:28:12.569 --> 00:28:14.130
You get Dominique on record?

622
00:28:14.154 --> 00:28:15.154
Yes.

623
00:28:17.365 --> 00:28:18.676
That's enough to hold.

624
00:28:18.700 --> 00:28:21.012
but you're gonna have to build more.

625
00:28:21.036 --> 00:28:22.245
Yeah. we will.

626
00:28:24.456 --> 00:28:27.060
[SIGHS]

627
00:28:27.084 --> 00:28:28.183
Okay.

628
00:28:28.207 --> 00:28:29.687
Bring him in.

629
00:28:29.711 --> 00:28:30.943
Hey.

630
00:28:31.960 --> 00:28:33.545
Move smart.

631
00:28:49.064 --> 00:28:50.671
Detective Foster.

632
00:28:51.942 --> 00:28:55.254
Hey. Officer Imani. Torres.

633
00:28:55.278 --> 00:28:56.756
You got a few minutes?

634
00:28:56.780 --> 00:28:59.550
Uh. sorry. Been a day.

635
00:28:59.574 --> 00:29:00.968
Any questions about your cold case

636
00:29:00.992 --> 00:29:02.595
are gonna have to wait.

637
00:29:02.619 --> 00:29:04.472
We understand. but we got something

638
00:29:04.496 --> 00:29:06.182
we need you to look at.

639
00:29:06.206 --> 00:29:07.725
We really would appreciate
your help on this.

640
00:29:07.749 --> 00:29:09.126
It won't take long.

641
00:29:12.546 --> 00:29:15.149
Really. now's not a good time.

642
00:29:15.173 --> 00:29:18.343
You're welcome to come back
tomorrow. okay?

643
00:29:27.728 --> 00:29:29.414
It's just a few questions.

644
00:29:29.438 --> 00:29:30.439
[ENGINE STARTS]

645
00:29:39.698 --> 00:29:41.300
[TAPPING]

646
00:29:41.324 --> 00:29:44.119
We'd really appreciate
your cooperation. Detective.

647
00:29:47.706 --> 00:29:49.146
Sure.

648
00:29:50.459 --> 00:29:52.210
You got it.

649
00:29:54.588 --> 00:29:57.316
We have evidence
corroborating our timeline.

650
00:29:57.340 --> 00:30:00.194
placing you at the scene
with each of our victims

651
00:30:00.218 --> 00:30:03.243
on or about the time of their murders.

652
00:30:03.638 --> 00:30:06.951
We have witness testimony
establishing your prior contact

653
00:30:06.975 --> 00:30:09.203
with Simone Morgan.

654
00:30:09.227 --> 00:30:11.622
And we have a witness who will testify

655
00:30:11.646 --> 00:30:14.333
that you were at the scene
of Noah Lewis's death.

656
00:30:14.357 --> 00:30:17.045
that you shot and killed him.

657
00:30:17.069 --> 00:30:18.379
and that you had motive to kill

658
00:30:18.403 --> 00:30:21.382
both Simone Morgan and Carter Thomas.

659
00:30:21.406 --> 00:30:23.075
That's three homicides.

660
00:30:27.120 --> 00:30:30.040
The sooner you talk.
the better your chances.

661
00:30:33.377 --> 00:30:34.858
That's all?

662
00:30:37.005 --> 00:30:38.900
This is ridiculous.

663
00:30:38.924 --> 00:30:40.948
You don't have enough to charge.

664
00:30:42.302 --> 00:30:45.744
So I'll just make myself
comfortable right here.

665
00:30:46.598 --> 00:30:48.622
That okay with you two?

666
00:30:50.269 --> 00:30:52.229
Go right ahead.

667
00:31:04.491 --> 00:31:06.868
Odell Morgan was
a good man. a smart man.

668
00:31:09.142 --> 00:31:10.602
He didn't give up.

669
00:31:11.206 --> 00:31:12.896
And I won't either.

670
00:31:16.753 --> 00:31:19.607
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

671
00:31:19.631 --> 00:31:26.596
♪ ♪

672
00:33:17.916 --> 00:33:19.644
- I got him.
- Good morning.

673
00:33:19.668 --> 00:33:21.521
There was a rug missing
from Morgan's living room.

674
00:33:21.545 --> 00:33:22.476
Okay.

675
00:33:22.500 --> 00:33:24.107
And the false witness. Carter. claimed

676
00:33:24.131 --> 00:33:25.441
he saw Odell carrying
the rug out to his car.

677
00:33:25.465 --> 00:33:27.193
We know that's a lie. but...

678
00:33:27.217 --> 00:33:29.070
The best lies are closest to the truth.

679
00:33:29.094 --> 00:33:31.572
So Foster would have needed
a vehicle to transport the rug

680
00:33:31.596 --> 00:33:33.157
and Simone's body out of the house.

681
00:33:33.181 --> 00:33:34.867
and he wouldn't have used
his police squad.

682
00:33:34.891 --> 00:33:36.202
He would have used his personal vehicle.

683
00:33:36.226 --> 00:33:37.704
And both of Foster's
vehicles at the time

684
00:33:37.728 --> 00:33:39.080
were two-door coupes.

685
00:33:39.104 --> 00:33:40.581
A rug wouldn't have fit inside.

686
00:33:40.605 --> 00:33:42.291
- So he borrowed another.
- He had to.

687
00:33:42.315 --> 00:33:43.835
But you wouldn't borrow
a friend's car for that.

688
00:33:43.859 --> 00:33:45.712
You wouldn't steal one. That's too hot.

689
00:33:45.736 --> 00:33:48.089
So I ran through all
of Foster's traffic stops

690
00:33:48.113 --> 00:33:50.049
that resulted in impound. and I found

691
00:33:50.073 --> 00:33:52.593
a gray Chevy pickup truck that
was scheduled to be destroyed.

692
00:33:52.617 --> 00:33:54.349
- Was it?
- No.

693
00:33:55.078 --> 00:33:57.223
That same Chevy pickup truck
was found missing

694
00:33:57.247 --> 00:33:58.766
the day after Simone's murder.

695
00:33:58.790 --> 00:34:01.144
There's no way that's a coincidence.

696
00:34:01.168 --> 00:34:03.587
Foster used that truck to dump the body.

697
00:34:04.755 --> 00:34:06.274
That's good work. Dante.

698
00:34:06.298 --> 00:34:07.942
[TENSE MUSIC]

699
00:34:07.966 --> 00:34:09.277
Call in the team.

700
00:34:09.301 --> 00:34:12.637
♪ ♪

701
00:34:17.665 --> 00:34:19.060
This was six years ago.

702
00:34:19.119 --> 00:34:20.532
The only traffic cams we have are what

703
00:34:20.556 --> 00:34:22.074
the lead detective saved.
and it's not a lot.

704
00:34:22.098 --> 00:34:23.624
Then we run historical
on all plate readers.

705
00:34:23.648 --> 00:34:24.998
- Is that saved?
- It should be.

706
00:34:25.022 --> 00:34:26.878
I got multiple hits on that
vehicle prior to that day.

707
00:34:26.902 --> 00:34:28.504
I got it.

708
00:34:28.528 --> 00:34:29.922
I got the Chevy going through
two different toll booths

709
00:34:29.946 --> 00:34:31.424
and an exit the night of the murder.

710
00:34:31.448 --> 00:34:32.717
And timeline matches.

711
00:34:32.741 --> 00:34:34.218
I got it around Wilmette.

712
00:34:34.242 --> 00:34:35.511
Check for a nexus.

713
00:34:35.535 --> 00:34:36.888
Wilmette and Brian Foster.

714
00:34:36.912 --> 00:34:37.996
Copy you.

715
00:34:39.748 --> 00:34:41.642
Yeah. I got nothing that ties him yet.

716
00:34:41.666 --> 00:34:42.727
The lake's out there.

717
00:34:42.751 --> 00:34:44.062
There's inlets. pockets.

718
00:34:44.086 --> 00:34:45.467
Enough to dump a body and a car?

719
00:34:45.491 --> 00:34:46.522
Possible.

720
00:34:46.546 --> 00:34:49.067
That's a damn good way
to make them disappear.

721
00:34:49.091 --> 00:34:50.360
Simone's there.

722
00:34:50.384 --> 00:34:51.569
- She's there.
- All right.

723
00:34:51.593 --> 00:34:52.862
What was the last hit on the toll booth?

724
00:34:52.886 --> 00:34:54.405
What exit?

725
00:34:54.429 --> 00:34:55.615
I got it.

726
00:34:55.639 --> 00:34:56.813
Dempster Road.

727
00:34:56.837 --> 00:34:58.330
Let's hit it.

728
00:34:58.809 --> 00:35:02.413
[HELICOPTER ROTORS THRUMMING]

729
00:35:02.437 --> 00:35:05.458
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

730
00:35:05.482 --> 00:35:12.447
♪ ♪

731
00:36:06.418 --> 00:36:08.275
[VOICE ECHOING] What are the chances...

732
00:36:10.338 --> 00:36:13.029
my van hits a police car this morning?

733
00:36:13.675 --> 00:36:15.778
Your car.

734
00:36:15.802 --> 00:36:18.489
What are the damn chances?

735
00:36:18.513 --> 00:36:20.491
Your car.

736
00:36:20.515 --> 00:36:23.077
It's fate?

737
00:36:23.101 --> 00:36:25.538
What else could it be?

738
00:36:25.562 --> 00:36:31.544
♪ ♪

739
00:36:31.568 --> 00:36:33.921
1070 to 5021 units.

740
00:36:33.945 --> 00:36:36.549
We got something
between 87th Street point

741
00:36:36.573 --> 00:36:37.592
and the breaker wall.

742
00:36:37.616 --> 00:36:38.718
Deploying divers now.

743
00:36:38.742 --> 00:36:45.707
♪ ♪

744
00:39:08.850 --> 00:39:11.496
Hey. my 48 must be up.

745
00:39:11.520 --> 00:39:12.747
If you have any more questions...

746
00:39:12.771 --> 00:39:14.916
Brian Foster. you're under arrest

747
00:39:14.940 --> 00:39:18.044
for the murders of Simone
Morgan and Noah Lewis.

748
00:39:18.068 --> 00:39:19.253
What?

749
00:39:19.277 --> 00:39:20.671
You have the right to remain silent.

750
00:39:20.695 --> 00:39:23.132
Anything you say can
and will be used against you

751
00:39:23.156 --> 00:39:24.680
in a court of law.

752
00:39:24.704 --> 00:39:26.886
What are you talking about?
You don't have anything on me.

753
00:39:26.910 --> 00:39:28.262
We have Simone's body.

754
00:39:28.286 --> 00:39:30.098
You have the right to an attorney.

755
00:39:30.393 --> 00:39:32.266
If you cannot afford an attorney.

756
00:39:32.290 --> 00:39:34.644
one will be provided for you.

757
00:39:34.668 --> 00:39:38.272
Do you understand these rights
as I have told them to you?

758
00:39:38.296 --> 00:39:41.109
[SOLEMN MUSIC]

759
00:39:41.133 --> 00:39:45.154
♪ ♪

760
00:39:45.178 --> 00:39:48.282
[CRYING]

761
00:39:48.306 --> 00:39:54.896
♪ ♪

762
00:41:28.115 --> 00:41:31.034
[WOLF HOWLS]

763
00:41:34.079 --> 00:41:37.058
[TENSE MUSIC]

764
00:41:37.082 --> 00:41:44.047
♪ ♪
